Notes:
- The API client used by the app lives at /services/api.ts (Platform-aware BASE_URL). There used to be a duplicate under /app/services which was treated as an Expo route and then removed/turned into placeholder.
- Backend provides REST endpoints: /products (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE), /products/:id (GET), /transactions (GET, POST), /transactions/:id (DELETE, PUT for notes), /login, /health, /reset (dev).
- DB file `backend/optom.db` contains seeded sample data if `products` table is empty.

If you'd like a different format (JSON, markdown tree, or including file sizes/modified times), tell me which format you prefer and I'll update `fayltuzilma` accordingly.